n helm with a feather plume on top. Under his armour he wears a white tunic, outlined with gold with two straps that come over each shoulder. His arms rest on the arm rests on his throne and he leans his head back on the throne. As his eyes waver across the lands far below he notices a place of great importance. His eyes linger upon the place for a few minutes. The god pushes off from the throne with his arms and then shifts all his weight onto his legs. He picks up a golden lance about 4 feet in length and a scaboard with a sheathed sword. The hilt of the sword is made of silver and has many jewels encrusted in it. He tosses the scaboard over his shoulder as well as a round shield made of gold. With his equipment ready the god floats down from Olympus to the mountain from which he can see old Ilion and Argos. Here is where Zeus navigated the Trojan war and Hera kept him aloof while making love to him. Poseidon sits down underneath a crevace which is overhead and puts his lance upon the floor. His armour clanks loudly as he sits down. He looks around and sighs with relief and satisfaction.::<br>
<br>
&quot;Mount Ida, the refuge of Zeus. A beautiful place it is, like Olympus, from which all things can be seen.&quot;<br>
 <p>Poseidon~Lord of the Sea</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A> at: 6/25/01 3:09:38 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 103<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/25/01 4:47:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mount Ida</span><hr size=1> :Poseidon looks over to the place Zeus sat with his deep blue eyes. Slowly rising to his feet Poseidon stands, leaving his lance on the ground. He walks over to Zeus' chair and rubs his hand gently along it. Turning he looks down Mount Ida, where none but the gods and immortals can come, and watches the mortals at their daily doings. He sits in Zeus' chair and makes himself comfortable.::<br>
<br>
&quot;I feel as if I now rule the world. That can only be a wish now. Zeus is invincibly strong and fast, and I only rate second to him.&quot;<br>
<br>
::Poseidon thinks back to when Zeus gave the Trojans power to crush the Danaans and sent Iris with message to him to leave the battle of Troy at once or he would personally come down to fight  him.::<br>
