A smile played itself across his delicate angelic face as he heared the unmistakable voice of his uncle Poseidon.<br>
<br>
He stepped to the thrown room, the shadows illuminated by his golden aura. He brought his hand to his mouth and clears his throat to make his presence known. He smiles to Poseidon and crosses his arms while leaning against a pillar, the whole time that same confident yet unaggressive smile on his face. His body adorned in asian robes, his hair unusually long;for him atleast. Yet his face remains without stubble. His crystilian eyes meet Poseidon.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ahh, tis the dream of most to hold that power that belongs to only and exclusivly to our Father God, the mighty Zeus. Tis it not dear Uncle? Yet it was a while ago, I was a still a boy, when he stated of the sweat to be broken by battling you his dearest and nearest of brothers. Since then times have changed.&quot; He nods saying just this as he moves to the balcony and grasps the railing, closing his eyes and smelling the crisp clean moutain air.<br>
<br>
&quot;I suggest that you, in sorts change your opinions or loyalty dearest Uncle. Tis me, Apollo that is second that to the almighty Zeus, along with my sister Athena. Though, yes we are no match for Zeus, I suggest you make sure you are alone when &quot;whispering&quot; your dreams to the world. For who knows? I could have been Zeus.&quot;<br>
<br>
 He crosses his arms and smirks, looking back at Poseidon.<br>
<br>
